<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO FRESHMAN BASKETBALL PLAYERS SUSPENDED BY LOYOLA FOR '94-95 SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two freshman basketball players have been suspended for the season by Loyola 
Marymount. 
</P>
<P>
 Terryl Woolery, a 6-foot-4 guard from Fairfax High, and Will Jones, a 6-5 
forward from Chicago, were suspended for "violation of the University's Student 
Conduct Code," according to a statement released by the school. 
</P>
<P>
 Neither played Sunday night in the Lions' 111-83 exhibition victory over Blue 
and Gold Fleet at Loyola. 
</P>
<P>
 Coach John Olive could not be reached for comment. 
</P>
<P>
 Two weeks ago, Olive called Woolery "a steal," adding: "He's going to be a 
very, very talented player." 
</P>
<P>
 Woolery was an All-City pick last season at Fairfax, averaging 16.5 points, 
7.8 rebounds and 4.3 assists. Jones averaged 10.8 points and 6.4 rebounds at 
Chicago Mt. Carmel High. 
</P>
