<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP VOLLEYBALL; STATE'S BEST SEEDED NO. 1 IN REGIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newport Harbor, the top-ranked team in the State, is seeded No. 1 for the 
Southern California region of the Division I State girls' volleyball 
championships and will play Millikan in a first-round match Tuesday at Newport 
Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sailors, also ranked No. 1 in the nation by USA Today and Volleyball 
Monthly, defeated Mira Costa, 15-5, 15-1, 15-7, in the Southern Section 
Division I final Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Second-seeded Mira Costa plays at Chatsworth in the first round. 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth, facing top-seeded Palisades for the City Section 4-A Division 
title last Saturday night at Occidental College, broke open a tight final game 
after midnight. 
</P>
<P>
 With Chatsworth ahead, 8-7, senior Jennifer Joseph served six consecutive 
points to boost second-seeded Chatsworth past the four-time defending champion 
Dolphins, 10-15, 16-14, 9-15, 15-11, 15-9, in a match that ended at 12:10 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach and Edison, semifinalists in the Southern Section Division I 
playoffs, are seeded first and fourth in the Southern California Division II 
state regional. 
</P>
<P>
 Bishop Montgomery (Division III), Calvary Chapel (Division IV) and Brentwood 
(Division V) are also seeded No. 1 for the Southern California Regionals. 
</P>
<P>
 Second-round matches are Saturday and the regional finals are Nov. 29. 
</P>
<P>
 The State finals, pairing the Southern California and Northern California 
regional winners, are Dec. 3 at Cal State Fullerton. MIKE ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
