<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL 1994-1995 / GOLDEN WEST LEAGUE; WESTMINSTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 1993-94 RECORDS 
</P>
<P>
 OVERALL: 10-15 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 5-9 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: RECORD AT SCHOOL 
</P>
<P>
 Dick Katz: 81-172 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P Amber Farroux 
Sr. 6-2 C Rachel Kavan Sr. 5-5 G April Ramirez Sr. 5-5 G Kristin Schult Jr. 6-2 
C 04,16,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Jennifer Lee Sr. 5-3 G Jennifer Lopez 
Sr. 5-5 G Sarah Patalano Sr. 5-1 G 04,15,05,06,05 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Lan 
Erickson Sr. 5-6 G/F Erin Moore So. 5-9 F Sarah Noland Sr. 5-11 F/C OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Now is the time for Westminster to be a playoff-contending team. With eight 
seniors and five juniors on this year's squad, there's no time like the 
present. Katz believes with Farroux and Schult, both 6-2, the Lions can compete 
with anyone in the paint. The two combined for 14 points and 13 rebounds per 
game last season. Farroux, who signed a letter of intent with Nevada Las Vegas, 
is expected to be one of the top players in the league. Both she and Kavan 
(eight points and three assists per game) are four-year varsity players with 
valuable experience. Ramirez (5.7 points) also has three years of varsity time 
under her belt. Along with their post game, Katz believes the Lions have good 
perimeter shooting and an excellent pressure defense. Seniors Noland (transfer 
from Estancia) and Erickson (transfer from Rancho Alamitos) will be asked to 
fit into the Lions' plan immediately. Moore, last year's junior varsity MVP, 
has excellent skills.  
</P>
