<HEADLINE>
<P>
FREEDOM BOWL GIVES UTAH ANOTHER SHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Utah, runner-up in the Western Athletic Conference, has been selected to play 
in the Dec. 27 Freedom Bowl, the bowl committee said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 It will be the second consecutive Freedom Bowl appearance for Utah (9-2).The 
Utes lost to USC, 28-21, last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Utah will face either Arizona or Washington State. The opponent will be 
determined after Arizona and Arizona State play Friday. The bowl coalition gets 
its pick of a Pac-10 team before the Freedom Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 If the coalition picks USC, Arizona would come to the game with a victory over 
Arizona State. If Arizona wins and is selected by the coalition, Washington 
State would play Utah. 
</P>
<P>
 By mutual agreement, USC will not make a third consecutive appearance in the 
game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
