<TEXT>
<P>
 Pianist Jody Chou, 13, of Irvine won the top prize Saturday in the Saddleback 
College music competition in Mission Viejo. Chou received $300 after playing a 
movement of Mozart's Concerto No. 19.Pianist Becky Kitamura, 22, of Mission 
Viejo took the second place award, $200; violinist Bertrand Yeung, 11, of 
Irvine won third place, $100. Pianist Helen Park, 16, of Diamond Bar placed 
fourth, and violinist Elbert Tzeng, 17, of Irvine was the runner-up. The three 
top winners will play with the Saddleback Symphony, conducted by Barry 
Silverman, at the college Feb. 11 and 12. Information: (714) 582-4747. 
</P>
<P>
 The Fullerton Museum Center is looking for volunteer docents to work on 
"Project Discovery," an educational tour program for young people. Those 
selected will work Tuesday through Friday mornings and will be instructed in 
touring technique. Interested persons are invited to a free informational 
buffet Dec. 9 at noon at the center, 301 N. Pomona Ave., Fullerton. Information 
and reservations: (714) 738-6545. 
