forces in Europe to become the airline's new vice president of corporate 
safety. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert C. Oaks, 58, left his military post earlier this year, ending a 35-year 
career. He also is a former chief of the Air Force's training organization, the 
Air Training Command. He starts Dec. 1. 
</P>
