COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: YORBA LINDA; LIGHTING CEREMONY AT NIXON LIBRARY TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Officials at the Richard Nixon Library & Birthplace will throw the switch on 
more than 1,000 Christmas lights tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 The annual lighting ceremony takes place in the library's garden at 6:30 p.m.  
</P>
<P>
 Although library officials decided not to light the 150-year-old pepper tree 
next to the Nixon birthplace, as has been done in the past, two smaller trees 
will have lights strung from their branches. 
</P>
<P>
 A community sing-along led by choirs from Bernardo Yorba and Travis Ranch 
middle schools will be held, and library volunteers will put on a short play. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is free and open to the public. The library is at 18001 Yorba Linda 
Blvd. Information: (714) 993-3393. DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
</P>
