<P>
 * Issues coming up 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 
</P>
<P>
 City Council meeting 
</P>
<P>
 When: 5:30 p.m. Tuesday 
</P>
<P>
 Where: Council Chambers, One Civic Center Plaza 
</P>
<P>
 What: The city's Public Works and Transportation Services departments will 
present an overview of the city's relationship to the San Joaquin Hills Toll 
Road project. In September, Assemblyman Gil Ferguson (R-Newport Beach) told 
council members the city could be entangled in lawsuits filed by county 
residents to keep tollbooths off Newport Coast Drive. Some residents testified 
against the plan at that meeting. "This will be a little more objective, 
informational kind of report," said Councilman Barry J. Hammond. "It will 
clarify the city's position in all of this." 
</P>
<P>
 More Information: (714) 724-6000 Brea-Olinda Unified 
</P>
<P>
 School board meeting 
</P>
<P>
 Where: Brea Civic and Cultural Center, 1 Civic Center Circle, Brea 
</P>
<P>
 When: 7:30 p.m. Monday 
</P>
<P>
 What: The school board is expected approve allowing two administrators and all 
seven trustees to attend the annual California School Board Assn. conference in 
San Diego this month. The district would pay $6,400 to have officials attend 
the conference. 
</P>
<P>
 More Information: (714) 990-7800 Huntington Beach 
</P>
<P>
 City Council meeting 
</P>
<P>
 When: 6:30 p.m. Monday  
</P>
<P>
 Where: Council chambers, 2000 Main St. 
</P>
<P>
 What: The council will conduct a public hearing to consider increasing the oil 
barrel tax and to impose a business license tax on rental properties of one or 
two units. A hearing will also be conducted to increase certain fees for the 
FireMed Program, the city's paramedic membership program. Another hearing is 
scheduled to establish provisions in the city's code to regulate carts and 
kiosks downtown. The council also will consider responding to Councilman David 
Sullivan's request that the city attorney prepare a directive for the release 
of gross salary information on all city employees without disclosing the 
identity of the employee holding a specific position. 
</P>
<P>
 More Information: (714) 536-5227 Orange 
</P>
<P>
 City Council meeting 
</P>
<P>
 When: 7 p.m. Tuesday  
</P>
<P>
 Where: Council chambers, 300 E. Chapman Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 What: The council will conduct a public hearing on a proposed change in the 
zoning code. The change would revise the permit process for businesses that 
want to sell alcoholic beverages. The code would restrict the ability of the 
Police Department to overrule permits granted by the Planning Commission 
because the alcohol would be sold in a high-crime area. 
</P>
<P>
 More Information: (714) 744-5500 
</P>
<P>
 The column is designed to offer a sampling of public meetings taking place in 
Orange County. For more information about meetings in your area, call your 
local government office. 
</P>
<P>
 -- COMPILED BY LESLEY WRIGHT, RUSS LOAR AND DEBRA CANO 
