<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City officials want you to think twice before throwing away your old telephone 
directories. 
</P>
<P>
 Recycling one ton of phone books saves about 17 trees and three cubic yards of 
landfill space, according to ecology experts. 
</P>
<P>
 So cities throughout Orange County are urging residents this month to recycle 
rather than dump their old phone books when the new 1994-95 directories arrive. 
</P>
<P>
 Some local trash haulers plan to give the discarded directories to paper mills 
for recycling. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about directory recycling, call your city hall or Pacific 
Bell at (213) 351-4016 Today 
</P>
<P>
 "Photography: Use and Abuse in the  
</P>
<P>
 Information Age" will be the topic of a free lecture by photography instructor 
Jerry Burchfield at Cypress College. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is scheduled for 7:30 p.m. in Room 205 of the college's technical 
education facility. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress College is at 9200 Valley View St., Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the event, call (714) 826-2220, Ext. 244. 
</P>
