<P>
PEOPLE: YAMAGUCHI SELECTED AS PRESIDENT OF TEAC AMERICA INC. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hajime (Jim) Yamaguchi has been elected president of Montebello-based TEAC 
America Inc. Yamaguchi, 49, who is responsible for all TEAC operations in the 
U.S., Canada, Central and South America, was previously senior executive vice 
president of the company. Yamaguchi succeeds Norio Tamura who was elected 
president of TEAC America's parent, Tokyo-based TEAC Corp. 
