<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: HOLLYWOOD BEACH; MAN SURRENDERS IN BARRICADE DRAMA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Hollywood Beach man armed with a shotgun held police at bay for more than 
six hours until negotiators talked him into surrendering, sheriff's officials 
said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Eugene Graves, 43, barricaded himself inside a beachfront home about 
10:15 p.m. Saturday, threatening to shoot himself because he was distraught 
over personal problems, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ventura County Sheriff's Department Special Weapons and Tactics team 
responded to the Los Robles Street residence, where Graves gave himself up 
about 4:30 Sunday morning, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 He was taken to a mental health facility for observation. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
