<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: 5 'DEADBEAT PARENTS' ON POSTER ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Five parents profiled on a wanted poster from the Ventura County district 
attorney's office have been arrested for failing to pay child support. 
</P>
<P>
 The most-wanted "deadbeat parents" poster spotlighting the county's worst 
suspected offenders was released Sept. 28.Since then, investigators have 
located four parents and another has turned himself in, Deputy Dist. Atty. C. 
Stanley Trom said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators arrested Jose Luis Leon, William Matuzak, Frances Quintana and 
Pedro Flores Villareal for failing to make child support payments. Miguel Angel 
Guevara turned himself in at Ventura County Municipal Court after seeing his 
photograph on the poster, Trom said. 
</P>
<P>
 The five parents owed more than $350,000 in court-ordered support payments, 
Trom said. 
</P>
<P>
 The district attorney's office has also received tips on the whereabouts of 
two other parents profiled on the poster, the fourth in a series to be 
displayed at grocery stores, banks and police stations throughout Ventura 
County, the prosecutor said. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
