<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: QUAKE AID DEADLINE EXTENDED TO JAN. 20 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The deadline to apply for earthquake disaster assistance has been extended to 
Jan. 20, three days after the one-year anniversary of the Northridge quake, 
federal and state officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The extension applies to applications for assistance from the Federal 
Emergency Management Agency's housing assistance program, the 
state-administered Individual and Family Grant Program, and the Small Business 
Administration's disaster loan programs for homeowners, renters and business 
owners. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is the final extension of the application period for the Northridge 
earthquake," said Frank Kishton, federal coordinating officer. "There will not 
be another extension." 
</P>
<P>
 Residents may register for assistance at any earthquake service center or by 
calling (800) 462-9029. Residents with hearing and speech disabilities should 
call (800) 462-7585. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
