<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: VILLA PARK; SANTA CLAUS COMING TO TOWN'S PARADE DEC. 17 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has picked Dec. 17 as this year's date for the city's annual 
Santa Claus Parade. 
</P>
<P>
 The yearly event is something like trick-or-treat and Mardi Gras wrapped in a 
Christmas theme.One of the annual event's highlights occurs when Santa and the 
five council members ride through town on a county fire engine. 
</P>
<P>
 The daylong ride through town starts about 8 a.m. and continues to about 5 
p.m. The fire engine goes down residential streets, and council members pass 
out candy to children. 
</P>
<P>
 Sometimes the colorful event is marred by rain. But by mayoral proclamation, 
it was announced recently that weather would be good Dec. 17. 
</P>
<P>
 "It will not rain this year," Mayor Barry Denes jokingly proclaimed. "It 
rained last year." BILL BILLITER 
</P>
