<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: THE SOUTHLAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Shopping Season Launch: Friday marks the official start of the 1994 Christmas 
shopping season -- the make-or-break selling time for most retailers.Most 
Southland shopping centers are preparing for the kickoff by opening their doors 
at 8 a.m., two hours earlier than normal. Surveys of local consumers and 
retailers show they expect holiday spending to increase this year. Many 
retailers and some industry analysts predict that demand for apparel will surge 
after several years of lackluster sales. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA112194-0190 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 100924 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
