<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: LOS ANGELES COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Report on Dangerous Toys: As the Christmas shopping season gets under way this 
week, the California Public Interest Research Group will release a list of toys 
it says could pose a risk to young children.The organization says 11 of the 24 
toys on the list violate federal small-parts standards for toys designed for 
children younger than 3. Children could choke by swallowing such parts, CalPIRG 
said. Others on the list, which will be released Tuesday, emit dangerous noise 
levels or contain toxic chemicals, the group said. Some of the toys are in 
packaging that lacks adequate warnings of possible dangers, it said. CalPIRG 
will discuss its findings Tuesday morning at Kaiser Permanente Hospital in West 
Los Angeles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
