<TEXT>
<P>
 Kemper-Conseco Merger Falls Apart: Kemper Corp. and Conseco Inc. have called 
off their proposed merger, less than three weeks after Conseco lowered its 
original $3.25-billion bid by $290 million.Conseco, a Carmel, Ind.-based 
insurance company, in June offered $67 a share for Long Grove, Ill.-based 
Kemper, which has interests in insurance and financial services. Kemper 
accepted. But on Nov. 2, Conseco said rising interest rates were making 
debt-financing more expensive and lowered its bid to $2.96 billion, or $60 a 
share. 
</P>
