<P>
 Rudman to Lead Nasdaq Panel: Former Republican Sen. Warren Rudman will lead a 
panel reviewing the operations of the Nasdaq computerized stock exchange and 
its governing body, the National Assn. of Securities Dealers Inc. Rudman will 
lead a seven-member committee in reviewing the effectiveness of Nasdaq and NASD 
-- the self-regulating body for Nasdaq. The Justice Department and the 
Securities and Exchange Commission earlier announced reviews of practices at 
the nation's second-largest stock exchange. 
