<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC WATCH: CHINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fixed-Asset Investment Slows: China's investment in fixed assets grew half as 
fast in October as it did in September due to government attempts to cool the 
economy. Economists watch fixed asset investment figures in China as a key 
inflation indicator and measure of economic overheating. The State Statistics 
Bureau reported that fixed asset investment by state units grew 22.5% in 
October over the year-earlier month, down from a 46.1% growth rate in 
September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
