<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Agency Declares Recession Officially Over: The Economic Planning Agency said 
the recession that crippled Japan for 30 months officially ended in October, 
1993. The recession, which the agency said began in May, 1991, is the second 
longest since the end of World War II, following a 36-month slump in the early 
1980s after the second oil shock. 
</P>
