</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Canada Gives Vietnam MFN Trading Status: Canada has agreed to give Vietnam 
most-favored nation trading status, doubled its textile export quotas and 
signed over a new chunk of aid. The textile export quota will be increased to 
two million pieces of clothing a year from next year from 1.1 million under an 
agreement which expires at the end of 1994. Canada will give Vietnam up to $27 
million in development assistance over the next four to five years for projects 
in economic management, legal and administrative reform and environmental 
management, officials said. 
</P>
