<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN, 19, SLAIN AFTER AN ARGUMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 19-year-old Pacoima man, who followed two men after an argument, died when 
he was shot in the head, authorities said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Raul Estrada and his cousin were at a fast-food restaurant Friday night when 
they exchanged harsh words with two men in a light yellow Cadillac Seville, 
said Los Angeles County Sheriff's Sgt. Ron Spear. 
</P>
<P>
 The men asked Estrada where he was from and when Estrada didn't answer, they 
drove off, Spear said. 
</P>
<P>
 Estrada and his cousin followed the two men to 60th Street West and Avenue K, 
where Estrada got out of his car and approached the other driver's window, 
Spear said. 
</P>
<P>
 "There was another exchange of words before the driver of the Cadillac said, 
'You punk,' and fired one round from a handgun, striking Estrada in the head," 
Spear said. 
</P>
<P>
 Spear said Estrada was pronounced dead at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 The two men drove north on 60th Street and are still at large, Spear said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
